🌿I am a self-taught calligrapher, engraver, arts & crafter, and painter
🌿during the day, I work in financial services but at night, my artist cap comes on. I started a new job yesterday so this account may see some quiet times (thanks for still following along!) 
🌿 I love reliving my childhood with my daughter and crafting with her #nancymoylife
🌿my feed is not curated anymore so expect to see a variety but lately it’s been calligraphy, plant tips, kids crafts, kids baskets, real talks, and whatever my latest obsession is (stay tuned for embroidered sweaters, garlands and poms) 💞

How cute are these mirror compact place settings?! Love this creative dual purpose place setting 💕 swipe for behind the scenes chaos and below for why calligraphers “charge so much”. We don’t “write quickly” - you’re paying for our time and skill to complete a project that has many steps #nancymoyevents
.
Rush orders throw a curve ball in an artist’s schedule. Here’s an idea of some of the things I consider/do:
✍🏼consultation time (trying to understand what the client wants and execute their vision). The best is when the client trusts me 100% and loves my style
✍🏼reshuffle existing orders to meet rush order deadlines. Often times, I end up working very late at night (this is time I could be spending with my family/friends or resting so that’s why artists charge rush fees)
✍🏼We can’t do everything in one day because that’s how we get carpal tunnel. Orders are spaced out. I’ve made this mistake before and the pain is scary!
✍🏼In this cascardshad even less time to complete 
✍🏼open the box and cut each plastic wrap neatly so I can repurpose them at the end
✍🏼clean the compacts prior to writing. Most surfaces must be cleaned/primed before writing 
✍🏼make one sample / send a photo for approval
✍🏼wait for approval (which delays when I can start)
✍🏼write on them neatly
✍🏼 repackage them into each sleeve and then pack into the box neatly so they don’t get damaged
✍🏼email client to coordinate pick up e.g., drop off with Uber or messenger

Today would have been my BFF’s 35th birthday. Can you believe it’s been 13+ months since her passing? I want to say the grief has gotten better but I think I’ve just found ways to not think about it and it eats me when I’m alone or when something reminds me of her. While Tiff found peace in God, I have not been able to do so. I know she would tell me to focus on the positives such as how strong & empathic her children will grow up to be and the positive lessons I am taking out of this grief but I am still so angry that her life ended this soon. Selfishly, I really needed her this past year.
.
These photos were from the last birthday we celebrated together. Before I turned 30, I remember telling her how alone and unaccomplished I felt and she ALWAYS knew the right things to say and do. She reminded me I was being absurd and all that I had accomplished. She knew that while words of affirmation was her love language, I was an actions person and she decided to plan a surprise birthday party for me! She always believed in family gatherings (something I’ve taken away from her and why I’ve been celebrating holidays with my child this year). I was blown away and it was exactly what I needed - a small, intimate gathering with my girlfriends and I felt so loved.  For her 30th, she didn’t want to go out nor celebrate because she was pregnant. I refused to take no for an answer and we celebrated at her home with Chinese food, cupcakes and our HS girlfriends.
.
For our 31st - 33rd birthdays, COVID and cancer got in the way. Don’t let life get in the way. Celebrate your birthday, celebrate your friend who had the courage to leave a broken relationship, celebrate that promotion, celebrate keeping your sh*t together after a bad day. Keep celebrating because we have to cherish the good times. If we don’t celebrate the milestones, what are we left with? 
.
If you made it this far, thanks for reading and the free therapy 🙏💕 if you would like to help, Tiff’s memorial link for her 3 young children is still saved in my story highlights if you’d like to donate or read more about her journey. Thank you! #nancymoylife #griefjourney #cancersucks #checkyourboobies

✏️curriculum / hours
